This paper deals with natural language processing and deep generative models, which are typically associated with the computer science sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The use of latent variables and the Gumbel top-k reparameterization technique suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper's emphasis on content planning and surface realization could also relate to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
